    <h3 class='text-center'>Toxicity?  No. Brain Permeability? Yes.</h3>
      <p>Toxicology screens commissioned by Prolume (ms in prep., H. Schmidt) did not reveal any toxicity concerns of CTZ, the luciferin we employ, consistent with our extensive experience with repeated administration of it in water-soluble form. Another FAQ is whether CTZ can reach brain targets. Multiple published studies and our ongoing work show that CTZ can access the brain (e.g., neocortex, Choroid Plexus) after peripheral injection.</p>
