                  <p id='Study_I'><b>Study I: Impacting Development with Chemogenetic LMO3 Activation, then Probing Changes in the Adult with Optogenetic Drive</b></p>
                  <p><a class='bl-link' href='https://doi.org/10.1016/j.isci.2021.102157' target='_blank'>Medendorp et al. 2021 </a> drove pyramidal neurons expressing LMO3 by IP CTZ injection P4-P10. They then used direct optogenetic drive of LMO3 to test adult excitability in the same cells. Adult mice showed robust behavioral and physiological changes after developmental BL-OG treatment.</p>
