                <div>
                  <br>
                  <p id='Study_IV'><b>Study IV: LMO3 Activation Drives Motor Recovery Following Spinal Cord Injury</b></p>
                  <p>Petersen et al. (in review; <a class='bl-link' href='https://doi.org/10.1101/710194' target='_blank'>bioRxiv</a>) expressed LMO3 in the ventral cord below an impact injury. Driving LMO3 activation with repeated CTZ injections (10 days) significantly enhanced the long-term recovery of motor coordination/control of the lower limbs, as compared to vehicle control treatment of injured mice.</p>
                </div>
